**![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)**

The action icons displayed at the top of the XML Reader's configuration page allow to perform global actions on the XML data structure.

**Icon**

**Action**

**Description**

![](data:image/png;base64,)

[**Import**](/doxee-platform/docs/2-dt3-xml-reader-global-actions#importing-a-data-schema)

Define the structure to write XML output files by importing an existing structure, schema, XML or XSD file.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

**Download structure**

Download a copy of the data structure to your local filesystem in XML format (for example: *Reader_1_structure.xml*).

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

**Settings**

Define the general settings of the XML Reader resource.

### Importing a data schema
This feature allows to define the structure to read XML input files using a previously exported Data Transformation schema or structure, or an external XML or XSD file.

The functionality is useful, for example, if you want to import the structure of an existing XML file instead of manually defining the required elements and attributes.

> Note

It is always possible to modify the imported data structure.

> Warning

This action will permanently delete and overwrite the existing data structure.

- Open the XML Reader resource in the configuration editor as described in [Configuring DT3 Project Resources](/doxee-platform/docs/configuring-dt3-project-resources).

- Click  ![](data:image/png;base64,) (**Import structure**). The system notifies you that uploading a structure file will discard the existing structure.

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

- Click **Yes, continue **to proceed.

- Select the required XML or XSD file to upload using the file browser. The new data structure is automatically loaded into the XML Reader's configuration, overwriting the existing data structure.

### Configuring the XML Reader's general settings
- Open the XML Reader resource in the configuration editor as described in [Configuring DT3 Project Resources](/doxee-platform/docs/configuring-dt3-project-resources).

- Click  ![](data:image/png;base64,) (**Settings**). The **Settings **panel is displayed on the right; for example:

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

- Configure the required parameters:

**Section**

**Parameter**

**Description**

**General**

**Name**

Name of the XML Reader

**Description**

*(optional) *Brief description of the XML Reader

**Schema**

**Schema name**

View and edit the name of the current data schema.

**Manage schemas**

Click on this link to manage the available data schema, as described in [Managing data schemas](/doxee-platform/docs/2-dt3-xml-reader-global-actions#managing-data-schemas) below.

**Defaults**

**Element**

Select the required option, in order to include (or exclude) the prefix of elements in the output XML file:

**Unqualified**: exclude prefix

- **Qualified**: include prefix

- Select the **Trim values **option if you want to delete any blank spaces from the elements of the input XML file.

**Attribute**

- Select the required option, in order to include (or exclude) the prefix of attributes in the output XML file:

**Unqualified**: exclude prefix

- **Qualified**: include prefix

> Tip

The **Applied to **section lists the Data Transformation components using this data schema, allowing you to evaluate the impacts of adding, deleting or modifying its elements.

#### Managing data schemas
- Click on the **Manage schemas **link to open the dedicated panel; for example:

![](data:image/png;base64,)

- Move your mouse over the name of a data schema to display the context actions; for example:

![](data:image/png;base64,)

- Select one of the available actions:

**Icon**

**Action**

**Description**

![](data:image/png;base64,)

**Download**

Download the data schema to your local filesystem.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

**Rename**

Edit the name of the data schema.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

**Delete**

Permanently remove the data schema from the project.

> Warning

This action cannot be undone.

If a data schema is currently used by one or more project components, this action is not available.

- If a data schema is used by one or more project components, a blue dot is displayed next to it. Click on it to see which resources are using the structure; for example:

![](data:image/png;base64,)

A detail panel listing the resources already using the selected structure is displayed; for example:

![](data:image/png;base64,)

> Tip

Click on the name of a resource to open it in its dedicated editor.

It is also possible to download or rename the data schema from this panel.
